- String must be defined in a string resource instead of hard coded
- DataBinding and ViewBinding must be used to bind the views
- Naming conventions must be followed
- Proper error handling must be implemented
- Function or method must be small and single responsibility, if it is doing more than one thing then it should be divided into multiple functions
- Function or method parameter must be in model class instead of passing multiple parameters, if more then 3 parameters are passed then it should be in model class
- Feature must be divided into multiple modules
- Proper package structure must be followed
- Must be follow the designed application architecture. MVVM, Clean Architecture.
- Try catch will not be used in the code, instead of try catch proper error handling must be implemented
- Application resources must be as per the design pattern